Celebrating our Seniors!
Class Night 2020-Additional Award Announcements

A few award announcements were inadvertently omitted or not yet available at the time of the recording of the Class Night 2020 video. To the students who were the chosen recipients of the awards that were omitted, we are sorry. Pandemic or no pandemic, it is always our intent to recognize the achievements communicated to us. We also apologize to the organizations and individuals associated with the omitted scholarships. Our school and its students are fortunate that the PORTA community places such importance on continued learning and your contributions are invaluable.The attached video includes the omitted announcements as well as others we have learned of between the date of the recording and now. This clip will also be added to the Class Night 2020 presentation available for viewing on YouTube.

post_text: Congratulations to Lauren Smith, who is the recipient of the PORTA Thespians award for 2020! The PORTA Thespian award is voted on by directors and peers, and it is an honored tradition at PORTA. This spring, Lauren would have played the role of Mother Abbess in “The Sound of Music.” Past roles include: Nerd in school for nerds, ancestor in The Addams Family, stage manager and student director for A Christmas Carol; A Live Radio Play, Marge in Bye-Bye Birdie, Student Director for Radium Girls and Erzulie the goddess of love in Once On This Island. Lauren is not only a joy to work with on stage, but she is also always willing to stay after, come early, or give up her study hall to help out with anything she can. Her beautiful voice and calm presence will be missed next year, but we look forward to seeing her continue to do great things!

Celebrating our Seniors!
Today, we are posting a few pictures sent in by our seniors showing us what they are doing during the school closure! Cooking, baking, fishing, drawing, completing scholarship applications and studying are just a few of the responses received when we asked what they were up to! Many are also serving the community as essential workers. Although this isn't the end of the school year they had imagined, it appears these seniors are making the most of a difficult situation! #BecauseweareBluejays

post_text:
Calling all Bluejays! Today would have been our fourth and final "Because I'm a Bluejay" day at the Jr-Sr High. Please accept our challenge to share in the Bluejay spirit by taking a moment to do something nice for someone today and post to your own social media and comment here with a picture. Earlier this year, we spent these afternoons working in teams to plan and carry out acts of kindness and service that represent various pieces of what it means to be a Bluejay. (Enjoy these photos from projects completed prior to the school closure!) Even though we can't be here together today, we would like to continue efforts to do something positive for others. Students, parents, community members, businesses, please join in! Show us your Bluejay spirit! We're in this together, even if we can't be together. Go Bluejays!
#BecauseweareBluejays #ILSchoolsStepUp #PORTAproud

post_text:
Celebrating our Seniors!
Today, we wish a fond farewell to our foreign exchange students, Abdullah from Turkey and Francesca from Italy! You have both become "Bluejays," and it was our hope that you would celebrate the end of the school year with the Class of 2020 in our traditional way. However, because of the current situation, that is not possible. Thank you both for spending time with us and sharing a bit of yourselves and your cultures with us. You brought joy to the lives you touched and contributed positively to the school and greater community. Safe travels! We will miss you and wish you all the best in the future!

Census 2020 is upon us!!
The 2020 Census is here, and important to your child’s future! This year’s Census will determine funding for local schools for the next 10 years, in addition to emergency services, roads, Medicare, Medicaid, community assistance programs like SNAP and more. Completing the Census is safe, easy, and completely confidential.

If you have questions about the Census or would like assistance completing it, please call Emma at the Cass County Health Department at 217-452-3057 ext. 1373. For more information, visit 2020census.gov.

post_text:
Preschool Screenings

PORTA-Greenview Preschool programs will be conducting a developmental screening for any preschool-aged children on March 17th and 18th at the Petersburg United Methodist Church. Areas to be checked include speech, language, movement skills, and basic concepts. The screening takes approximately 1 hour to complete.
Children turning 3 & 4 before September 1st, who are living in the PORTA or Greenview School District, are encouraged to attend. If your child is not age-eligible at the time of screenings, but will be 3 in August, please bring them. Please don’t wait to have your child screened! Our program fills up quickly, and then students go on a waiting list. Children must be screened in order to be considered for the 2020-2021 PORTA-Greenview Preschool programs.
To make an appointment, please call Petersburg Elementary School (632-7731), option 2.

Music is available by emailing rreid@porta202.org Please contact her with any questions you might have about this event.

post_text:
Due to the weather, the IHSA Class 2A Girls’ Basketball Regional games scheduled for this evening have been postponed until tomorrow evening, using the same time schedule.

In particular, Pittsfield schools have an early dismissal today, and so their administration has requested that the games be postponed, and we are in agreement with that assessment.

The championship game will still be played on Friday evening (and the 3-pt shootout will be on Friday evening as well).

post_text:
PORTA JH Scholastic Bowl A Team went 5-1 and finished 2nd place out of 16 teams in the Small School Division of the Metcalf Sweetheart Tournament. Way to go, Bluejays!
Scores: we beat Metcalf D 140-45; beat Corpus Christi B 130-70; beat Flanagan A 195-155; beat Cornerstone Christian Academy A 185-95; lost to Next Generation A 75-215 (the eventual champs); beat Normal Epiphany Catholic A 160-140 in a super exciting match. Trace Donnan answered the most toss ups with 16, and Billy Thornton answered 9.

post_text: The Friends of PORTA FFA will be holding their 5th annual fundraiser on Tuesday, February 4th in the PORTA High School Commons. Serving will begin at 5:00 pm and continue until 7:00. The menu will consist of a ribeye sandwich or hamburger, chips, cookie, and water. The ribeye meal will be $6.00 and the hamburger meal will be $5.00. The Menard County Farm Bureau will also be sponsoring a half-court shot. Funds will be used to help PORTA FFA members. Come enjoy a great meal and support PORTA FFA! Stay to cheer on your favorite High School Boys' Basketball team as the Bluejays host the Athens Warriors. The PORTA Jr. High wrestling will be hosting the Beardstown Tigers. Also, come out to support the little girls' cheer and dance team! Come enjoy a night of great food and great athletic competitions!
